Interpretation:
  For every all-plus prefix Q, next label q, and boundary target a absent
  from the extended plus support, the mode constructs C_Q and
  E_Q=H(C_Q e_0)-C_Q exactly.  It verifies
    E_(qQ)(a,k)
      =sum_(u in a star_k q)E_Q(u,k)
        +E_Q(a,k-q)-E_Q(k-a,q)
  against a direct reconstruction after adjoining q, and requires the
  resulting boundary entry to be nonnegative.  The individual-reservoir
  counts are negative diagnostics, not failures of the combined target.
  The fully-disjoint count additionally requires q to be new and both sink
  terminals k-a,q to be absent from Q.  The displayed level-five example
  proves that both reservoirs are essential even after these reductions.
